title: Coordinator Interview
Interview Descriptions: Really friendly and helpful lovely people and great interview process with lots of support for applicants. Great charity to work for but just didn’t have the hours   I needed. Would recommend to anyone
Interview Questions: Why did I want to do the job

title: Director, Human Resources Interview
Application Type: I applied online. I interviewed at Home Start (San Diego, CA) in Jun 2020
Interview Descriptions: The Director of HR expressed interest in learning more about me and requested that I respond to 10 questions with a deadline date given. Zero contact or follow up took place after providing those responses.
Interview Questions: Tell me about experiences you've had in the non-profit sector.

title: Supervisor Interview
Application Type: I applied online. I interviewed at Home Start (San Diego, CA)
Interview Descriptions: Two panel interviews, approx. 45 minutes each, the entire process took about 3 weeks, questions regarding diversity, working under stressful conditions, prior work experience working with children, knowledge of child development stages, etc.
Interview Questions: Why are you interested in this position at this time?

title: Sales Associate/Cashier Interview
Application Type: I applied through other source. The process took 2 weeks. I interviewed at Home Start (San Diego, CA) in Jan 2016
Interview Descriptions: The interview was really about getting to know my past work experience and to see what my availability was. I was not nervous since I knew other girls that worked there. It was at the thrift boutique on the patio.
